reviews.text:
Class of 1971  had a get together last night.
Waitress was excellent with our large party. Food was excellent as well. Everyone had a wonderful time.

I had such a great experience at Fisher's eating for one, let me elaborate. Even though the restaurant was busy on a Saturday night, I was seated at my own table (most places will ask you to sit at the bar). Then, when I learned that the dish I wanted (Swordfish) was out, my server, Karen, checked several times with the kitchen to help find me an alternative and to include the other sides I really wanted, which were delicious: garlic butter baked halibut, fresh asparagus, shrimp risotto and cornbread with a whipped honey butter. I then ordered the fried ice cream, which was pretty incredible, though a bit much for one person. That's the good side of things.

Karen my server was authentic, she checked on me a couple times and when she saw I wasn't going to finish my I've cream, insisted I bring it home. Only trouble was, I wasn't going home, I was camping with my trailer, only I didn't have a place to park it for the night because all the camp sites in the area required advanced bookings. I told Karen this and she immediately started telling me about call sites in the area she knew about. I called one and they had a sitev available, but the fee was too high.

Karen asked her manager and they offered for me to camp in the back parking lot of the restaurant. To clarify, this post is not intended to turn Fisher's into a campsite, but to thank Karen for her kindness, care and help, which was immense.

Fisher's Pub is highly recommended if your passing through it visiting the Middleboro area.
Amazing service from Tessa G, she helped me select my new favorite meal (The Jumbo Hotdog) it‚Äôs so flavorful and delicious, couldn‚Äôt ask for anything better.

I've only been one time but they had some really good homemade chicken veggies soup! Then I had chicken veggie stir fry that was great and enough to tak home! So good! Server was fast and efficient and also nice her name was Amy! ( Thanks Amy)
Definitely going back üòä

Good restaurant to get good dinner.

We went on a Thursday night at the end of summer. They have a big parking lot. The hostess attended us very quick and placed us on a very nice table by the TVs.

The waiter came very quick and took our order drink order right away. She came back a little after and took our order.

Food came very fast and very good cooked. We love the fries. They tasted very fresh. I was impressed with the pico de gallo. It was just the right amount on the tacos. I was also impressed with the portions. They have very good portions. The fish tacos may seem small on the pictures but they are big, not your regular fish tacos size.

We will definitely come back.
